Package <Unnamed>

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Convertator
    The Convertator application is a converting calculator.
    CvtrCustom
    The Convertator Custom class displays a window to customize units, constants, or pre-defined equations.
    CvtrData
    The Convertator Data maintains information about the Data fields which are stored in Convertator format files.
    CvtrEngine
    The primary function of the Convertator Engine class is to parse an equation that contains units, convert the values to a common unit, calcalate the result, and convert it to the requested unit.
    CvtrFile
    The Convertator File class manages input and output of data in files.
    CvtrGroup
    The Convertator Group class parses an equation stack to separate it into groups of operations which are enclosed in parentheses.
    CvtrHistory
    The Convertator History class allows undos in the equation text field.
    CvtrImport
    The Convertator Import class displays a window to download units, constants, or pre-defined equations from a website.
    CvtrMessages
    The Convertator Message class handles several different types of messages.
    CvtrModifyResult
    The Convertator Modify Result class is used to change the base, units, precision, and scientific notation choice of a Result.
    CvtrOperand
    The Convertator Operand is a container for operand data.
    CvtrPrefs
    The Convertator Preferences maintains information about equation result fields so that the base and units may be changed easily.
    CvtrResult
    The Convertator Result maintains information about equation result fields so that the base and units may be changed easily.
    CvtrUnit
    The Convertator Unit maintains information about the Units field which is used for equation conversions.
    CvtrUpdate
    The Convertator Update class maintains information about Convertator updates used for downloads from a website.
    CvtrWeb
    The Convertator Web class downloads files from a web address.
    CvtrWindow
    The Convertator Window class builds the window and its components for the converting calculator user interface.
